    <article class="prose-editorial cs-body" set:html={`<h3><b>Educational Case Study Disclosure</b></h3><p>This case study is hypothetical and for educational purposes only. Scenarios, borrower profiles, loan terms, interest rates, and outcomes are illustrative examples and do not represent current offers or guaranteed terms.</p><p>For specific details including down payment requirements, closing cost estimates, interest rate details, closing cost breakdowns, payment calculations, cash-to-close estimates, or an official Loan Estimate, it is highly recommended you<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> schedule a meeting with one of our licensed mortgage advisors</a>.</p><p><b>Learn more:</b></p><ul><li><a href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/rules-policy/regulations/1026/24/">Stated income loan cash-out refinance Reg Z advertising requirements (§1026.24)</a> – CFPB official regulation</li><li><a href="https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-12/chapter-X/part-1026">Stated income loan cash-out refinance Reg Z full text and compliance</a> – Electronic Code of Federal Regulations</li><li><a href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/rules-policy/regulations/1026/interp-24/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Official stated income loan cash-out refinance advertising interpretations (§1026.24)</a> – CFPB interpretations</li><li><a href="https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-12/chapter-X/part-1014" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stated income loan cash-out refinance MAP Rule (Reg N) mortgage advertising</a> – Mortgage advertising rules</li><li><a href="https://www.nmlsconsumeraccess.org/">NMLS Consumer Access – Verify stated income loan cash-out refinance lender licensure</a></li></ul><p>Actual loan terms vary by credit profile, property, occupancy, location, market conditions, and lender guidelines. For current options tailored to you,<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> schedule a consultation</a> or<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/same-day-approval/"> apply online</a>.</p><p>Ready to explore your options?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> Schedule a call</a> with a loan advisor.</p>		
					<h2>See How Stated Income Loan Cash-Out Refinance Unlocked Capital for Business Growth</h2>				
		<p>David R., a 47-year-old architect who founded his own design firm in Fort Lauderdale, had built a highly successful practice over fifteen years specializing in luxury residential and boutique commercial projects. His firm generated substantial revenue through multiple income streams: architectural design fees, project management consulting, partnership income from joint venture developments, and occasional speaking fees at industry conferences. Despite strong six-figure income, David's tax returns showed significantly reduced earnings due to legitimate business deductions for software, equipment, continuing education, marketing, and operational expenses that his CPA strategically deployed to minimize tax liability.</p><p>David's primary residence had appreciated substantially over the decade he'd owned it, building significant equity. He had identified a perfect opportunity to purchase a small commercial building that would house his growing architectural firm while generating rental income from additional office suites. The building acquisition required substantial down payment capital that he could access through his home equity, but he needed cash-out refinancing to unlock those funds.</p><p>What David didn't anticipate was that traditional lenders would reject his cash-out refinance request despite his perfect mortgage payment history, excellent credit, and obvious business success. Conventional lenders couldn't calculate his income from his complex business structure with multiple income sources, making cash-out refinancing impossible through traditional channels even though he clearly had the financial capacity to handle increased debt.</p><p>Facing similar challenges?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> Schedule a call</a> to explore your options.</p><h2><b>The Challenge: Why Traditional Lenders Refused Cash-Out Refinancing for Business Expansion</b></h2><p>David contacted four conventional mortgage lenders confident that his perfect payment history, substantial home equity, excellent credit, and strong business income would make cash-out refinancing straightforward. Every lender rejected his application within days—some within hours.</p><h3><b>Why Do Traditional Lenders Reject Stated Income Loan Cash-Out Refinance for Self-Employed Borrowers?</b></h3><p>Traditional mortgage lenders view cash-out refinancing as higher risk than rate-and-term refinancing because borrowers are extracting equity and increasing their debt obligation. This heightened scrutiny makes conventional income documentation requirements even more stringent for cash-out refinances—creating nearly impossible barriers for self-employed borrowers whose tax returns understate their true earning capacity.</p><p>While rate-and-term refinances maintain or reduce debt, cash-out refinances increase borrowed amounts, requiring conventional lenders to prove borrowers can handle larger debt service. When income calculations from tax returns fall short of requirements—even for borrowers with perfect payment histories and obvious financial success—conventional lenders must deny applications regardless of the borrower's actual financial capacity.</p><h3><b>What Made David's Income Too Complex for Conventional Cash-Out Refinancing?</b></h3><p>David's business income structure presented multiple challenges for traditional underwriters:</p><p><b>Multiple income sources across business entities:</b></p><ul><li>Architectural design fees through professional corporation</li><li>Project management consulting income as separate LLC</li><li>Partnership K-1 income from joint venture development projects</li><li>Speaking fees and teaching income from university courses</li><li>Income spread across Schedule C, K-1 forms, and corporate returns</li></ul><p><b>Tax return complexities:</b></p><ul><li>Substantial business deductions reducing taxable income</li><li>Depreciation of computers, software, and office equipment</li><li>Continuing education and professional development expenses</li><li>Marketing, conference, and professional association costs</li><li>Business reinvestment in staff, technology, and growth initiatives</li></ul><p>"I run a highly successful architecture firm with strong consistent revenue and profit," David explained. "But my tax returns are structured to minimize taxes through legitimate business deductions—exactly what my CPA should be doing. Traditional lenders looked at my tax returns and calculated qualifying income far below my actual earnings. Even though I've paid my mortgage perfectly for years and clearly earn substantial income, they couldn't approve cash-out refinancing based on their rigid formulas."</p><h3><b>How Did Tax-Efficient Business Structure Prevent Equity Access?</b></h3><p>David's accountant had structured his architectural practice to maximize legitimate business deductions and minimize tax liability—smart business management that reduced his tax burden but made traditional mortgage qualification nearly impossible.</p><p><b>David's actual financial situation:</b></p><ul><li>Strong consistent income from successful architectural practice</li><li>Fifteen years of perfect mortgage payment history</li><li>Excellent credit score maintained throughout business ownership</li><li>Substantial home equity from property appreciation</li><li>Significant liquid reserves and retirement savings</li><li>Clear business opportunity requiring capital deployment</li><li>Obvious ability to handle increased debt from cash-out refinancing</li></ul><p><b>How traditional lenders saw David's situation:</b></p><ul><li>Complex tax returns with income from multiple sources</li><li>Business deductions reducing calculated qualifying income</li><li>Income appearing insufficient for increased debt obligation</li><li>Complex underwriting requiring extensive documentation analysis</li><li>High risk of denial despite strong actual financial position</li></ul><p>"My CPA does exactly what he should—minimize my taxes legally while maintaining excellent records," David said. "But that tax efficiency makes accessing my own home equity through cash-out refinancing impossible with traditional lenders. I'm not asking for charity—I have substantial equity, perfect payment history, and strong income. I just need lenders who can verify my income through actual deposits rather than tax return calculations that understate my earnings."</p><h3><b>Why Did Business Expansion Opportunity Require Quick Capital Access?</b></h3><p>The commercial building David identified was competitively priced and attracting interest from other buyers. Without quick access to down payment capital through cash-out refinancing, David risked losing the property to faster-moving buyers with simpler financing situations or cash offers. The building would house his firm rent-free while generating rental income from other suites—a perfect wealth-building investment that required immediate action.</p><p>"Real estate opportunities don't wait for lengthy mortgage processes," David explained. "I needed to act quickly to secure this building, but traditional lenders said their underwriting would take months—if they could even calculate my income at all from my complex tax returns. Speed and certainty matter in real estate acquisitions, and traditional cash-out refinancing offered neither."</p><p>Experiencing similar rejection?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> Schedule a call</a> to discuss alternative qualification methods.</p><h2><b>The Discovery: How David Found Stated Income Loan Cash-Out Refinance Programs</b></h2><p>David discovered<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/stated-income-loan/"> stated income loan cash-out refinance</a> programs through his commercial real estate broker who had worked with other business owners facing similar documentation challenges. The broker explained that stated income lenders verify earning capacity through bank statements and overall financial strength rather than complex tax return income calculations—particularly valuable for business owners seeking to deploy capital strategically.</p><p>"My broker said stated income cash-out refinance programs focus on verifying that I actually earn what I claim by reviewing bank deposits, not by trying to calculate income from complicated tax returns," David explained. "They understand that successful business owners often show reduced income on tax returns due to legitimate deductions, but their bank accounts tell the true story of their earning capacity."</p><h3><b>What Makes Stated Income Loan Cash-Out Refinance Different from Traditional Cash-Out Refinancing?</b></h3><p>The stated income loan advisor explained that stated income cash-out refinance programs evaluate borrowers through bank statement income verification, asset documentation, existing payment history, and overall financial profile rather than rigid tax return income calculations. For cash-out refinances, stated income lenders focus on whether borrowers have demonstrated financial responsibility and actually earn sufficient income to handle increased debt—verified through bank deposits and asset accumulation rather than tax formulas.</p><p><b>Stated income loan cash-out refinance advantages:</b></p><ul><li>Income verified through consistent bank deposits, not tax calculations</li><li>Existing perfect payment history demonstrates financial responsibility</li><li>Bank statement analysis shows actual cash flow and earning patterns</li><li>Asset verification proves financial stability and wealth accumulation</li><li>Business success evaluated through actual performance, not tax returns</li><li>Strategic capital deployment considered part of evaluation</li></ul><p>"The stated income approach made perfect sense for my situation," David said. "They verified my income by reviewing consistent strong deposits from my architectural practice into my bank accounts—proving I actually earn substantial income regardless of what my tax returns show. They considered my perfect payment history as evidence I manage debt responsibly. They evaluated the business opportunity I was funding with the cash-out proceeds. That comprehensive analysis captured my true financial situation far better than conventional formulas."</p><h3><b>How Do Stated Income Lenders Evaluate Cash-Out Refinance Applications?</b></h3><p>The stated income loan advisor reviewed David's complete cash-out refinancing profile:</p><p><b>Payment history and credit verification:</b></p><ul><li>Years of perfect mortgage payment history</li><li>Excellent credit scores maintained consistently</li><li>No delinquencies or financial problems throughout homeownership</li><li>Clear evidence of responsible debt management</li></ul><p><b>Bank statement income verification:</b></p><ul><li>Extended months of business bank statements from architectural firm</li><li>Personal bank statements showing consistent deposits from business</li><li>Cash flow patterns demonstrating strong regular income</li><li>Verification that claimed income matches actual deposits</li></ul><p><b>Asset and equity documentation:</b></p><ul><li>Current home appraisal showing substantial appreciation and equity</li><li>Investment and retirement account statements showing accumulated wealth</li><li>Business account balances demonstrating operational financial strength</li><li>Overall net worth supporting increased debt capacity</li></ul><p><b>Business opportunity evaluation:</b></p><ul><li>Commercial building purchase details and investment analysis</li><li>Rental income projections from additional office suites</li><li>Business expansion strategy and long-term growth plans</li><li>Exit strategy and risk management for capital deployment</li></ul><p>"The stated income lender evaluated everything comprehensively," David explained. "My perfect payment history, my bank statements showing consistent strong income from my practice, my substantial assets accumulated over fifteen years of business success, and the solid business opportunity I was funding. That complete picture proved I could easily handle the cash-out refinance and use the proceeds strategically for wealth building."</p><h2><b>The Solution: Stated Income Loan Cash-Out Refinance Approval and Funding</b></h2><p>David worked with his stated income loan advisor to compile comprehensive documentation that verified his income through bank statements, demonstrated his financial strength through payment history and assets, and explained his strategic capital deployment plans.</p><h3><b>What Documentation Did David Provide for Stated Income Loan Cash-Out Refinance?</b></h3><p>Stated income loan cash-out refinance requires thorough documentation verifying income, financial capacity, and strategic use of proceeds:</p><p><b>Payment history and existing mortgage documentation:</b></p><ul><li>Perfect mortgage payment history over years of homeownership</li><li>Current mortgage statement showing balance and terms</li><li>Payment verification through bank statements or servicer records</li><li>Payment history on all other obligations</li></ul><p><b>Bank statement income verification:</b></p><ul><li>Extended months of business bank statements from architectural firm</li><li>Personal bank statements showing deposits from business operations</li><li>Consistent cash flow patterns demonstrating regular strong income</li><li>Verification of all income sources and deposits</li></ul><p><b>Asset, equity, and net worth documentation:</b></p><ul><li>Current home appraisal confirming substantial appreciation and equity</li><li>Investment account statements showing significant liquid assets</li><li>Retirement account balances demonstrating long-term wealth accumulation</li><li>Business account statements confirming operational financial strength</li><li>Overall net worth statement supporting increased debt capacity</li></ul><p><b>Credit and business verification:</b></p><ul><li>Credit reports from all bureaus showing excellent scores</li><li>Business licenses, entity documentation, and professional credentials</li><li>Portfolio of completed architectural projects demonstrating success</li><li>Client testimonials and industry recognition</li></ul><p><b>Cash-out proceeds use documentation:</b></p><ul><li>Purchase contract for commercial building</li><li>Rental income projections from additional office suites</li><li>Business expansion strategy and growth plans</li><li>Investment analysis showing strategic capital deployment</li><li>Evidence of closing costs and down payment requirements</li></ul><p>"The documentation told a complete story of my financial strength and strategic thinking," David said. "Bank statements proved my income through actual deposits, payment history demonstrated responsibility, assets showed wealth accumulation, and my business expansion plan explained how I'd use the cash-out proceeds strategically. The stated income lender verified everything thoroughly but through methods that actually captured my true financial situation."</p><h3><b>How Long Does Stated Income Loan Cash-Out Refinance Take?</b></h3><p>The stated income lender moved efficiently through David's cash-out refinance application:</p><ol><li><b>Initial consultation</b> - Reviewed cash-out goals and income documentation situation (Day 1)</li><li><b>Preliminary approval</b> - Confirmed stated income cash-out refinance would work (Day 3)</li><li><b>Document submission</b> - Uploaded bank statements, payment history, business documentation (Day 5-7)</li><li><b>Payment history verification</b> - Confirmed years of perfect mortgage payments (Day 8-10)</li><li><b>Bank statement analysis</b> - Verified income through consistent deposit patterns (Day 10-15)</li><li><b>Asset and credit review</b> - Confirmed excellent credit and substantial net worth (Day 12-16)</li><li><b>Property appraisal</b> - Home appraised confirming strong equity position (Day 15-22)</li><li><b>Business opportunity review</b> - Evaluated commercial building purchase plans (Day 18-24)</li><li><b>Underwriting approval</b> - Approved based on complete financial profile (Day 26)</li><li><b>Clear to close</b> - Final approval issued with cash-out amount confirmed (Day 32)</li><li><b>Closing</b> - Successfully closed cash-out refinance (Day 40)</li></ol><h3><b>What Terms Did the Stated Income Loan Cash-Out Refinance Provide?</b></h3><p>David secured stated income loan cash-out refinance terms that provided substantial equity access while maintaining manageable debt structure:</p><ul><li><b>Conservative loan-to-value ratio</b> leaving significant remaining equity in home</li><li><b>Competitive interest rate</b> for stated income loan cash-out refinancing</li><li><b>Long-term fixed-rate structure</b> providing payment predictability</li><li><b>Substantial cash-out proceeds</b> sufficient for commercial building down payment</li><li><b>Manageable monthly payment</b> well within income capacity</li><li><b>No prepayment penalties</b> allowing future refinancing flexibility</li></ul><p>"The stated income loan cash-out refinance terms were excellent," David explained. "The rate was competitive considering the alternative documentation approach, the cash-out proceeds gave me exactly the capital I needed for the commercial building purchase, and the payment remained very manageable relative to my income. Most importantly, the approval came in weeks rather than the months traditional lenders said they'd need—if they could approve me at all."</p><p>Exploring refinance?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/refinance-or-heloc-inquiry/"> Submit a refinance inquiry</a> to compare your options.</p><h2><b>The Results: Commercial Building Acquired, Business Expanded, Wealth Building Accelerated</b></h2><p>David closed his stated income loan cash-out refinance approximately six weeks after starting the application. The cash-out proceeds funded the commercial building purchase that transformed his business operations and wealth-building trajectory.</p><h3><b>What Results Did David Achieve with Stated Income Loan Cash-Out Refinance?</b></h3><p><b>Final cash-out refinance outcome:</b></p><ul><li>Successfully accessed substantial home equity through cash-out refinancing</li><li>Conservative loan-to-value ratio leaving significant remaining equity</li><li>Competitive interest rate for stated income loan cash-out refinance</li><li>Manageable monthly payment well within income capacity</li><li><b>Timeline:</b> Application to closing in 40 days</li><li><b>Property:</b> Primary residence, Fort Lauderdale, FL</li><li><b>Perfect payment history preserved</b></li></ul><p><b>Commercial building acquisition and business impact:</b></p><ul><li>Used cash-out proceeds for down payment on commercial building</li><li>Relocated architectural firm to owned building (eliminating rent expense)</li><li>Generated rental income from additional office suites in building</li><li>Rental income from other suites covers substantial portion of building mortgage</li><li>Firm operates rent-free while building appreciates</li><li>Increased firm credibility and professional image</li></ul><p><b>Long-term wealth-building impact:</b></p><ul><li>Building equity in both primary residence and commercial property</li><li>Eliminated monthly rent expense, improving business cash flow</li><li>Rental income from other suites generates passive income</li><li>Commercial building appreciating in Fort Lauderdale market</li><li>Diversified wealth across residential and commercial real estate</li><li>Created generational wealth through strategic capital deployment</li></ul><h3><b>How Did Stated Income Loan Cash-Out Refinance Compare to Traditional Attempts?</b></h3><p><b>Traditional lender attempts vs. stated income loan cash-out refinance:</b></p><ul><li><b>Traditional lender qualification:</b> Rejected due to complex income documentation</li><li><b>Stated income lender qualification:</b> Approved through bank statement verification</li><li><b>Capital accessed:</b> Substantial cash-out proceeds enabling business expansion</li><li><b>Timeline:</b> Traditional uncertain and lengthy; stated income completed in 40 days</li><li><b>Business opportunity:</b> Stated income made commercial building purchase possible</li><li><b>Wealth-building strategy:</b> ACHIEVED ✓</li></ul><p>"The stated income loan cash-out refinance unlocked capital that traditional lenders said I couldn't access," David said. "I've built a successful architecture practice over fifteen years, paid my mortgage perfectly, maintained excellent credit, and accumulated substantial assets. The stated income lender recognized that financial strength by verifying my income through bank deposits rather than tax returns structured to minimize taxes. Now I own the building my firm operates from, generate rental income from other suites, and I'm building wealth across multiple real estate assets. That's the power of accessing your own equity with the right financing partners."</p><h3><b>What Are David's Next Steps After Successful Cash-Out Refinancing?</b></h3><p>The commercial building David purchased with his cash-out refinance proceeds has transformed both his business operations and his wealth-building trajectory. His architectural firm operates rent-free in owned space, the rental income from other suites covers most of the building mortgage, and the property appreciates in Fort Lauderdale's strong commercial market.</p><p>"Owning my own commercial building changed everything," David explained. "I eliminated substantial monthly rent expense, improved my cash flow, generated passive rental income, and built equity in commercial real estate. Now I'm considering purchasing an investment property—potentially a small multifamily building or vacation rental—to further diversify my wealth beyond my business and real estate holdings."</p><p>When David is ready to acquire additional investment properties, he may use a<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/heloc/"> HELOC</a> or<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/home-equity-loan/"> Home Equity Loan</a> on his primary residence or commercial building to access capital for down payments without refinancing and losing favorable rates. He's also considering<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/dscr-loan/"> DSCR Loans</a> for investment properties that eliminate personal income verification entirely.</p><p>"The stated income loan cash-out refinance experience taught me that strategic capital deployment accelerates wealth building far faster than keeping equity trapped in real estate," David reflected. "I accessed my home equity, purchased an income-producing commercial building, eliminated rent expense, and positioned myself for continued real estate investing. Now I'm building generational wealth across multiple asset classes using financing programs that understand business owner finances rather than penalizing tax-efficient structures."</p><p>Ready to get started?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/same-day-approval/"> Get approved</a> or<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> schedule a call</a> to discuss your situation.</p><h2><b>Exploring Other Stated Income Loan Options?</b></h2><p>While David used stated income loan cash-out refinance to access equity for business expansion, stated income financing works for multiple scenarios:</p><ul><li>Need to reduce rate? See how a<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/stated-income-loan-refinance/"> restaurant owner achieved monthly savings with stated income loan refinance</a></li><li>Purchasing investment property? Learn how an<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/stated-income-loan-purchase"> entrepreneur used stated income loan for property acquisition</a></li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/">View all case studies</a> to find success stories matching your goals</li></ul><h2><b>Key Takeaways for Business Owners Seeking Equity Access</b></h2><ul><li><b>Stated income loan cash-out refinance verifies income through bank deposits rather than tax return calculations</b>—particularly valuable for business owners whose tax returns understate actual earnings due to legitimate deductions and tax-efficient structures that reduce taxable income (<a href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/">Understanding alternative documentation mortgages</a>)</li><li><b>Strategic capital deployment accelerates wealth building</b>—accessing home equity to purchase income-producing commercial real estate or expand business operations creates multiple wealth-building engines rather than leaving capital trapped as dormant equity</li><li><b>Perfect payment history and asset accumulation prove financial capacity</b>—stated income cash-out refinance lenders evaluate complete financial profiles including payment history, bank statement income verification, and accumulated assets rather than relying solely on tax return formulas (<a href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/rules-policy/regulations/1026/">Mortgage lending regulations</a>)</li><li><b>Business opportunity evaluation matters for cash-out refinancing</b>—stated income lenders consider how borrowers will deploy cash-out proceeds, favoring strategic investments in income-producing assets, business expansion, or other wealth-building activities rather than pure consumption</li><li><b>Think strategically about diversifying wealth across asset classes</b>—successful business owners benefit from diversifying beyond business ownership into income-producing real estate, building passive income streams and generational wealth rather than concentrating everything in businesses</li></ul><p>Have questions about stated income loan cash-out refinance for equity access?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> Schedule a call</a> with a loan advisor today.</p><h2><b>Alternative Loan Programs for Business Owner Equity Access</b></h2><p>If stated income loan cash-out refinance isn't the perfect fit, consider these alternatives:</p><ul><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/bank-statement-loan/">Bank Statement Loan</a> – Cash-out refinance using bank deposits rather than tax returns</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/heloc/">HELOC</a> – Access equity through revolving credit line</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/home-equity-loan/">Home Equity Loan</a> – Fixed second mortgage for equity access</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/asset-based-loan/">Asset-Based Loan</a> – Qualify using liquid assets rather than income</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/portfolio-loan/">Portfolio Loan</a> – Flexible cash-out refinancing for unique situations</li></ul><p><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/">Explore all loan programs</a> to find your best equity access solution.</p><h2><b>Helpful Stated Income Loan Cash-Out Refinance Resources</b></h2><p><b>Learn more about this loan program:</b></p><ul><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/stated-income-loan/">Complete Stated Income Loan Guide</a> - Detailed requirements, rates, and qualification guidelines</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-calculator/stated-income-loan-calculator">Stated Income Loan Calculator</a> - Estimate your available equity and payments</li></ul><p><b>Similar success stories:</b></p><ul><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/stated-income-loan-refinance/">How a restaurant owner reduced payments with stated income loan refinance</a> - Rate reduction success</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/stated-income-loan-purchase">Entrepreneur purchases investment property with stated income loan</a> - Alternative documentation purchase</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/">View all case studies</a> - Browse by your situation</li></ul><p><b>External authoritative resources:</b></p><ul><li><a href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/">Understanding alternative documentation mortgages</a> - Consumer Financial Protection Bureau guidance</li><li><a href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/rules-policy/regulations/1026/">Mortgage lending regulations</a> - Federal lending standards</li></ul><p><b>Ready to get started?</b></p><ul><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/same-day-approval/">Apply online</a> - Start your cash-out refinance application</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/">Schedule a consultation</a> - Discuss your equity access strategy</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/discovery-quiz/">Take the discovery quiz</a> - Clarify your goals</li></ul><p>Need local expertise?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/get-a-local-introduction/"> Get introduced to trusted partners</a> including CPAs specializing in business owners, commercial real estate brokers, and investment advisors who understand wealth diversification.</p>		
